				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>This is an original approach, and very self-conscious about the act of writing; you have to mentally dig at what&#8217;s going on here, which make it dense and interesting. I was a bit confused by the initial pickle/spanner relationship, which didn&#8217;t quite seem to follow (maybe you use a spanner to open a pickle jar that&#8217;s closed too tightly?), but I liked the morphing of the image into taking &#8220;a firm grip on your imagination&#8221; and twisting.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

